# Bun Runtime & Package Manager

This project uses **Bun** exclusively — not Node.js.

- Use `bun` to run scripts, not `node`
- Use `bun install` / `bun add` / `bun remove` for dependency management, not `npm` or `yarn`
- Use `bunx` instead of `npx`
- Use `bun test` for running tests
- The project is packaged with a bundled Bun binary — do not assume Node.js is available at runtime
- Prefer Bun-native APIs (e.g., `Bun.serve`, `Bun.file`, `Bun.write`) over Node.js equivalents when available
